manufacturerProductDescription.media_text: MK335 Wireless Combo Entertainment at your fingertips Want to watch your favorite movie? Skip a song? Go right to your email or Facebook page? With multimedia and Internet hot keys, programmable F-keys and a comfortable sculpted mouse, this wireless combo makes it easy to access and navigate the things you do the most.

Designed for what you love You can get right to your favorite websites, music and movies thanks to 12 hotkeys, including 4 you can customize to open favorite apps and more. Happy hands Low-profile, whisper-quiet keys and a sleek design make for an uber-comfortable typing experience with laptop, netbook and desktop computers. Navigate in comfort The full-size mouse gives you smooth, accurate cursor control and effortless scrolling. The contoured design with soft rubber grips feels good in either hand, even after long hours of use. Media controls Skip a song. Pause a video. Turn up the volume. You get 11 multimedia hot keys for instant access to play, pause, previous, next, volume and mute. Plug-and-play simplicity Setup couldn’t be easier. A single included USB receiver connects both the keyboard and mouse to your computer. Just plug it in and go. Extended battery life Up to 24-month keyboard and 18-month mouse battery life* mean you can go a long time without the hassle of changing batteries.
System Requirements Windows XP, Windows Vista, Windows 7, Windows 8USB port

reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Wireless Ergonomic Keyboard

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 16, 2022
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars A Good General-Purpose Keyboard and Mouse Combo
reviews.reviewText: Well-made and responsive; a great bargain for a general-purpose mouse and keyboard set, with phenomenal battery life and a good keyboard feel. However, definitely not a keyboard for gaming, as the action is a common membrane keyboard action and not a microswitch-based keyboard; also, you should never game with a wireless mouse and keyboard due to lag. Lag that's unnoticeable in a wireless keyboard/mouse combo for general use can be very problematic when gaming. It also has an impressively long range; I've used one to do presentations where the keyboard/mouse was at least 20-25 feet from the receiver on the PC. One last note: Be very careful unpacking your new mouse and keyboard combo, as Logitech can't seem to decide where to put the all-important wireless receiver. Some models hide it in the mouse (a black, unmarked nub inside a black mouse, where it all blends together), others under the liner in the box, while some put it in a little sleeve next to the keyboard. Very easy to miss and accidentally throw away.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 7, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Best mouse/ keyboard combo out there
reviews.reviewText: Bought one of these 7 years ago and it finally gave out. Just bought another cause I love it so much!

Purchased when this was on sale. Great price for a office setup. I have used this for a couple months now and this has been a great addition to my office setup. Will definitely recommend to future buyers if they want a great keyboard for everyday or an office setup at an incredible price.

Edit Mar 7/21: Logitech customer support was helpful and easy to deal with. They sent me another set and though the mouse wheel is still a bit noisy the keyboard and mouse both work as they should.Edit Feb 17/21: The keyboard started lagging and/or not working at all intermittently after a month, and the mouse occasionally lags now but the scroll wheel has gotten quieter and more responsive. After trying every tip and troubleshoot possible I've found nothing that fixed the keyboard issue and it had been very frustrating to try to use it since it typed nothing much of the time. As of today the keyboard has stopped working at all and I'm using my ancient keyboard to type. I've bought Logitech products for many years and recommended them to everyone, until now. I would not recommend this set, there are now many bad reviews online and the intermittent issue is very common.Original review: Bought this set to replace my 10+yr old Logitech set. The keys are quite loud and feel a bit loose and the plastic housing feels cheaper than the old one, but it's laid out well and I like a full size keyboard. The mouse is also quite loud, especially the scroll wheel, and feels less well made than the old one. Everything works, but I've only had it a day so can't speak to longevity
Quieter than my old keyboard. Wife and I work side by side and she loves the quietness of this KB.
